                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>همایون نامه</p>
                            <p>A fine old copy of the Humáyún-náma, the well-known Turkish version
                                of the Anwár-i Suhaylí (Fables of Bidpáy), composed by 'Alí Chelebi
                                of Philippopolis (d. A.H. 950/1543) and dedicated to Sultán
                                Sulaymán I. See Rieu, B.M.T.C., pp. 227-228; Flügel, Vienna Cat.,
                                vol. III, pp. 299-301.</p>
                            <p>Begins:</p>
                            <p>حضرت حليم خلّاق و حكيم على الاطلاق جلت حكمته</p>
                            <p>Ff. 345 of 24 x 16.2 c. and 21 ll. Excellent ta'líq with
                                rubrications. Transcribed by Khalíl ibn Yúsuf in Jumádà I, 982
                                (August, 1574). According to Professor Browne's note on the
                                fly-leaf, this MS. was given to him in April, 1908, in
                                Constantinople by Dr Rizá Tevfiq.</p>
                        </summary>
